.
1. Enable in menuconfig for buildroot to build exfat
./build.sh buildroot menuconfig
2. Enbale in menuconfig for kernel to build fuse
./build.sh kernel menuconfig
3. Load root.axfs and xipImage to board, test:

/*format SDXC to exFAT*/
$ mkfs.exfat /dev/mmcblk0p2
mkexfatfs 1.2.4
Creating... done.
Flushing... done.
File system created successfully.

/*This time, mount failed due to unsupport exFAT*/
$ mount /dev/mmcblk0p2 /tmp/
mount: mounting /dev/mmcblk0p2 on /tmp/ failed: Invalid argument

/*Show information of exFAT SD*/
$ dumpexfat /dev/mmcblk0p2
dumpexfat 1.2.4
Volume label                        
Volume serial number      0xd58363e1
FS version                       1.0
Sector size                      512
Cluster size                  131072
Sectors count              120539136
Free sectors               120534016
Clusters count                470841
Free clusters                 470836
First sector                       0
FAT first sector                 128
FAT sectors count               3712
First cluster sector            3840
Root directory cluster             4
Volume state                  0x0000
FATs count                         1
